1
00:00:01,102 --> 00:00:04,105
(slow twangy music)

2
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:20,254
- All right, pal,
 rise and shine.

3
00:00:21,422 --> 00:00:25,093
What do I look like,
 an alarm clock?

4
00:00:25,093 --> 00:00:26,360
Let's move.

5
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,462
You're just askin'
 to get a whuppin'.

6
00:00:28,462 --> 00:00:31,865
Haven't even gotten
 my cup of coffee yet.

7
00:00:47,481 --> 00:00:48,816
Come on, let's go.

8
00:00:48,816 --> 00:00:49,950
Up, up.

9
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:51,285
- What time is it?

10
00:00:51,285 --> 00:00:53,154
- Don't give me that garbage.

11
00:00:53,154 --> 00:00:55,123
- Look, I'm just tryin'
to put a little sunshine

12
00:00:55,123 --> 00:00:56,590
in your life, Dinah.

13
00:00:56,590 --> 00:01:00,394
- Child, when I need
 sunshine, I'll ask for it.

14
00:01:02,196 --> 00:01:03,731
(hand knocking)

15
00:01:03,731 --> 00:01:04,565
- Yeah?

16
00:01:12,673 --> 00:01:15,943
- All right, Murell,
 it's your big day.

17
00:01:15,943 --> 00:01:17,311
Ready for your job assignment?

18
00:01:17,311 --> 00:01:20,414
- Yeah, let me guess,
 doctor, lawyer,

19
00:01:22,783 --> 00:01:24,051
game show host?

20
00:01:24,051 --> 00:01:25,319
(laughing) Let me
 see what you got.

21
00:01:25,319 --> 00:01:28,689
- Sorry, hon, they gave
those jobs out already.

22
00:01:28,689 --> 00:01:30,591
We just get the leftovers.

23
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:32,593
- I'm a janitor.

24
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:34,928
- Shouldn't be too tough for ya.

25
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:37,097
Think you can handle it?

26
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:38,699
- It's up a church.

27
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:43,504
- That's right, now get
it together, Murell.

28
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:45,673
We're counting on you.

29
00:01:45,673 --> 00:01:48,776
You've been at this
place for 3 1/2 months.

30
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:51,212
- Four, counting rehab.

31
00:01:51,212 --> 00:01:53,814
- Whatever, four months.

32
00:01:53,814 --> 00:01:55,816
It's a big step for you.

33
00:01:56,984 --> 00:01:58,786
You ever held a job before?

34
00:01:58,786 --> 00:02:00,188
- No, not really.

35
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:04,725
The only job I was any
 good at was dealin'.

36
00:02:04,725 --> 00:02:07,060
- We sleep about 135 men here.

37
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:10,298
Sometimes in the winter,
 we've had as many as 200,

38
00:02:10,298 --> 00:02:11,799
and we try to get
 as many of these men

39
00:02:11,799 --> 00:02:13,967
out into the
 community as possible

40
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,337
so that they can
 get full-time jobs.

41
00:02:16,337 --> 00:02:17,871
And if you'll come
 with me, I'll show you

42
00:02:17,871 --> 00:02:21,809
the counseling center
 and the women's quarters.

43
00:02:21,809 --> 00:02:23,477
- Hey, I can see it.

44
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:33,321
- Hi, my name is Murell.

45
00:02:36,824 --> 00:02:37,991
What's yours?

46
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,593
- Come on, girls, let's go.
 - Amy.

47
00:02:39,593 --> 00:02:40,428
- Hi, Amy.

48
00:02:50,404 --> 00:02:52,139
- [Dinah Voiceover]
 God'll use your gifts.

49
00:02:52,139 --> 00:02:53,807
Just follow through
 on that commitment

50
00:02:53,807 --> 00:02:56,009
to Christ you made a
 couple of months ago.

51
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,611
You gotta trust him.

52
00:02:57,611 --> 00:02:59,747
He'll take care of the rest.

53
00:02:59,747 --> 00:03:01,482
You can do it, Murell.

54
00:03:01,482 --> 00:03:05,185
Now show these people what
 you got goin' for you.

55
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,854
(slow twangy music)

56
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:08,088
- Stay up, now.

57
00:03:14,595 --> 00:03:18,332
- Keep your eyes on the
things above, Murell.

58
00:03:27,174 --> 00:03:28,175
- All right,

59
00:03:29,577 --> 00:03:33,213
last week we were talking
 about the Beatitudes.

60
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,982
Any questions so far?

61
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:38,986
Yeah.

62
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:41,455
- Yeah, um, how much
 longer is this gonna take,

63
00:03:41,455 --> 00:03:43,624
'cause I'm missing my MTV.

64
00:03:44,925 --> 00:03:47,328
- Okay, um, let's take a look

65
00:03:48,962 --> 00:03:52,132
at the passage in chapter five.

66
00:03:52,132 --> 00:03:53,967
What does he mean when he says,

67
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:58,138
"Blessed are the meek for
 they shall inherit the earth?"

68
00:03:59,139 --> 00:03:59,973
No idea?

69
00:04:03,143 --> 00:04:03,977
Anybody?

70
00:04:07,114 --> 00:04:09,517
What's he talking about here?

71
00:04:11,385 --> 00:04:14,888
- He's just sayin'
that we should be meek.

72
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,292
- Okay.

73
00:04:20,428 --> 00:04:21,261
What else?

74
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,703
Come on, we talked about this.

75
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:35,275
(motor revving)

76
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:40,448
- Check it out!

77
00:04:40,448 --> 00:04:41,515
It's a Ninja!

78
00:04:44,852 --> 00:04:47,421
- Hey, guys, come on, sit down.

79
00:04:50,924 --> 00:04:53,827
All right, come on,
 let's finish up.

80
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:55,829
Just a few more minutes.

81
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:00,968
Okay, well,

82
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:06,139
maybe it's time for a break.

83
00:05:10,944 --> 00:05:13,447
(sighs)

84
00:05:13,447 --> 00:05:16,116
(strings music)

85
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:27,828
- [Man] Now, what
 are you planning

86
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:29,563
for this section of the lot?

87
00:05:29,563 --> 00:05:31,565
- The rear entrance would
 be here, and there'll

88
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:32,900
be plenty of room for parking.

89
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,768
And the north annex
will be right over here.

90
00:05:34,768 --> 00:05:37,004
- And you want all
 this done by December?

91
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:39,172
There's absolutely no way.

92
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,563
- Need some help
with that, Jack?

93
00:06:02,563 --> 00:06:04,998
- Uh no, thanks, I've got it.

94
00:06:22,182 --> 00:06:24,084
- Now, I spoke with
Mr. Conroy, and he said

95
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:26,086
there'd be no problem
 meeting the deadline.

96
00:06:26,086 --> 00:06:28,656
- Well, look, he obviously
 didn't realize the extent--

97
00:06:28,656 --> 00:06:31,391
(Murell sighing)

98
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:34,394
Can I help you with something?

99
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:37,230
- Hmm, I'm from
 the Thompson House

100
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:41,435
shelter, here.

101
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:48,876
- Oh yes, yes, of course,
 well, why didn't you say so?

102
00:06:48,876 --> 00:06:50,277
Linda mentioned you'd be coming.

103
00:06:50,277 --> 00:06:51,512
Linda?

104
00:06:51,512 --> 00:06:52,746
- [Linda] Yes.

105
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:54,448
- Linda, this is the
 man from the shelter.

106
00:06:54,448 --> 00:06:57,485
Um, I'm sorry,
 what is your name?

107
00:06:57,485 --> 00:06:59,587
- Murell, Murell Parsons.

108
00:07:00,988 --> 00:07:02,255
- Linda will you show
 Murell where the cleaning

109
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,557
supplies are kept and
 just briefly acquaint

110
00:07:03,557 --> 00:07:04,792
him with his duties here?

111
00:07:04,792 --> 00:07:06,259
- Certainly.

112
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,928
Oh, by the way, Howard asked
 me to give this to you.

113
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:09,963
He said you should
 read it immediately.

114
00:07:09,963 --> 00:07:11,865
Oh. (laughing)
 - Thank you.

115
00:07:11,865 --> 00:07:13,901
- [Linda] He said it
 was very important.

116
00:07:13,901 --> 00:07:15,669
- Now, where were we?

117
00:07:16,904 --> 00:07:20,007
- [Linda] You'd
 better read it now!

118
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:22,743
- I'm sorry, would
 you excuse me?

119
00:07:33,521 --> 00:07:36,957
With this I submit my
 formal resignation?

120
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:42,696
Hold on just one minute.

121
00:07:55,509 --> 00:07:59,046
- Here it is,
everything you'll need.

122
00:07:59,046 --> 00:08:02,449
Oh, here is your weekly routine,

123
00:08:02,449 --> 00:08:05,118
and these are your work clothes.

124
00:08:10,891 --> 00:08:12,760
Oh, we'll have to fix that.

125
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,095
What did you say
 your name was again?

126
00:08:15,095 --> 00:08:16,163
- Uh, Murell.

127
00:08:17,898 --> 00:08:21,969
- I don't think they have
 a label with that name.

128
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:28,742
(gentle music)

129
00:08:41,188 --> 00:08:43,090
Ugh, somebody should've
water those things.

130
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,825
They're in pretty bad shape.

131
00:08:44,825 --> 00:08:47,427
- No, actually they'll be fine,

132
00:08:48,562 --> 00:08:52,332
just need a little
 water, a little light.

133
00:08:52,332 --> 00:08:55,535
- I gave them some plant
food once, didn't help.

134
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:59,740
- No, just give 'em
 light and some water,

135
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:01,942
but only the proper amount.

136
00:09:03,343 --> 00:09:05,012
They just need love.

137
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:15,989
(loud piano music)

138
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:49,522
- Everything's set
 with the janitor.

139
00:09:49,522 --> 00:09:51,859
He's a bit of a strange one.

140
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:56,129
Guess he's been waiting a while.

141
00:09:57,665 --> 00:09:59,767
By the way, the youth group
 is gathered downstairs

142
00:09:59,767 --> 00:10:02,335
right now, apparently,
 they're unsupervised.

143
00:10:02,335 --> 00:10:04,204
- Please, tell me you're joking?

144
00:10:04,204 --> 00:10:08,375
- Walter, don't forget your
 stress management techniques.

145
00:10:12,412 --> 00:10:14,414
- Hmm, what we got here?

146
00:10:16,549 --> 00:10:18,719
Mop the floors, vacuuming,

147
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:25,158
wash the windows,
 empty the garbage.

148
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:31,398
Man, what am I doin' here?

149
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,143
(kids laughing)

150
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,251
- [Boy] Yes!

151
00:11:00,227 --> 00:11:03,463
- Janitor, somebody spilled
 some drinks over there.

152
00:11:03,463 --> 00:11:05,532
Could you go clean it up?

153
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:29,289
- Couldn't anyone teach
these kids to clean

154
00:11:29,289 --> 00:11:30,791
up their own mess?

155
00:11:33,593 --> 00:11:37,230
- Hey man, why did you
become a janitor anyway?

156
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:39,032
- 'Cause that's
 all he's good at.

157
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:40,968
Can't do anything else.

158
00:11:42,836 --> 00:11:45,338
- Oh, what makes you say that?

159
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:20,473
(drum music)

160
00:13:10,891 --> 00:13:12,492
Oh, uh, sorry, sir.

161
00:13:14,294 --> 00:13:16,296
I was just about to um...

162
00:13:16,296 --> 00:13:19,900
- And perhaps you'd
better get right to it.

163
00:13:22,502 --> 00:13:24,838
- Nice playin', drummer boy.

164
00:13:33,413 --> 00:13:37,584
- Now, everyone, I have some
 disappointing news for you.

165
00:13:47,394 --> 00:13:49,462
- Man, I mean, I'm sorry.

166
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:09,316
Um, I gotta get
 somethin', excuse me.

167
00:14:12,085 --> 00:14:12,920
Ugh.

168
00:14:17,424 --> 00:14:18,258
- Sorry.

169
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:27,700
- [Man] Well, we
 lost another one.

170
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:28,936
- Oh, no.
 - What's it gonna take

171
00:14:28,936 --> 00:14:30,437
to get someone?
 - That's four now.

172
00:14:30,437 --> 00:14:32,739
- This is really costing us.
 - In what, about three years?

173
00:14:32,739 --> 00:14:34,707
- This one seven months.
- This is absolutely

174
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:36,209
intolerable.

175
00:14:36,209 --> 00:14:38,045
Why exactly are they quitting?

176
00:14:38,045 --> 00:14:39,612
- [Board Member]
 Money, could it be?

177
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:42,349
- Walter, we've
 gotta do something.

178
00:14:42,349 --> 00:14:44,484
People are getting concerned.

179
00:14:44,484 --> 00:14:47,354
You know, I had a parent call
 me at 10 o'clock last night.

180
00:14:47,354 --> 00:14:50,690
- We can't just put the
youth program on hold.

181
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:52,292
You know how these
 parents complain

182
00:14:52,292 --> 00:14:55,228
when their kids are sitting
 at home on Wednesday nights.

183
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:56,930
- Well look, if we could
just put the youth group

184
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:59,799
on a temporary hiatus
for a couple of months.

185
00:14:59,799 --> 00:15:01,601
I have a candidate
 all picked out.

186
00:15:01,601 --> 00:15:05,338
He's graduating with his
 Master's from Fuller in June.

187
00:15:05,338 --> 00:15:06,573
I've already screened him.

188
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:08,575
He's the perfect choice.

189
00:15:15,382 --> 00:15:18,718
- Sure, that's what you
said about the last one,

190
00:15:18,718 --> 00:15:20,287
and look how long
 he stuck around.

191
00:15:20,287 --> 00:15:23,756
- (laughing) Seven months!

192
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:26,926
- Okay, okay, I know I've
 made some poor judgments

193
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:30,463
in the past, but
 this guy is terrific.

194
00:15:30,463 --> 00:15:32,265
He has a gift for
 working with kids.

195
00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:34,034
- That's all well
 and good, Walter,

196
00:15:34,034 --> 00:15:36,303
but we can't afford
 to wait two months.

197
00:15:36,303 --> 00:15:39,039
We need a replacement right now.

198
00:15:39,039 --> 00:15:41,574
It doesn't look good for
 a 500-member congregation

199
00:15:41,574 --> 00:15:43,977
to be lacking a youth pastor.

200
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:54,854
(squeegee squeaking)

201
00:16:11,171 --> 00:16:14,007
- You're doing it wrong.

202
00:16:14,007 --> 00:16:14,841
Here.

203
00:16:42,269 --> 00:16:43,103
You'll do fine.

204
00:16:43,103 --> 00:16:44,404
Hang in there.

205
00:16:44,404 --> 00:16:46,973
(gentle music)

206
00:17:02,355 --> 00:17:03,623
- We'll give you till
 Friday to come up

207
00:17:03,623 --> 00:17:05,725
with a replacement, Walter.

208
00:17:05,725 --> 00:17:07,460
- And then what?

209
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:08,795
- I don't know.

210
00:17:08,795 --> 00:17:11,164
I'm hoping we won't
 get to that point.

211
00:17:11,164 --> 00:17:14,000
(group muttering)

212
00:17:21,108 --> 00:17:23,676
(gentle music)

213
00:17:36,523 --> 00:17:38,558
- Hey, what are doin'?

214
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:40,327
- What does it look
 like I'm doin'?

215
00:17:40,327 --> 00:17:41,494
- You go to this church?

216
00:17:41,494 --> 00:17:44,097
- Yeah, only because I have to.

217
00:17:46,866 --> 00:17:49,035
- Hey, you're pretty good.

218
00:17:50,637 --> 00:17:53,306
Here, let me show you something.

219
00:17:54,741 --> 00:17:55,575
Here.

220
00:17:57,009 --> 00:17:58,345
- What?

221
00:17:58,345 --> 00:18:01,448
- I just wanted to
 show you somethin'.

222
00:18:55,001 --> 00:18:55,935
- Are you okay?

223
00:18:55,935 --> 00:18:57,904
- Whew, yeah, I'm all right.

224
00:18:57,904 --> 00:19:00,540
I was just tryin' to show
 you my backwards side flip.

225
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:03,109
- You haven't been here
too long, have you?

226
00:19:03,109 --> 00:19:05,144
- No, about a week.

227
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,846
- Were you a janitor
 somewhere else?

228
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:09,015
- No, not really.

229
00:19:09,015 --> 00:19:10,383
- What did you do then?

230
00:19:10,383 --> 00:19:13,720
- I was living in a
 shelter in the city.

231
00:19:17,089 --> 00:19:18,225
- Oh.

232
00:19:18,225 --> 00:19:19,559
- Murell.

233
00:19:19,559 --> 00:19:21,294
- Oh, uh, sorry.

234
00:19:21,294 --> 00:19:24,130
I was just finishing
 up over here.

235
00:19:32,038 --> 00:19:34,341
- Murell, I wanted to
ask you a few questions.

236
00:19:34,341 --> 00:19:35,308
May I?

237
00:19:35,308 --> 00:19:36,709
- Sure, go ahead.

238
00:19:38,578 --> 00:19:40,880
- Have you ever worked
 with young people before?

239
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,882
- Yeah, well, kinda.

240
00:19:42,882 --> 00:19:45,685
I used to help out at
the boys club sometimes.

241
00:19:45,685 --> 00:19:47,320
- I see.

242
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:49,889
Ever been in a leadership
 capacity of any kind?

243
00:19:49,889 --> 00:19:50,723
- No.

244
00:19:54,261 --> 00:19:56,796
- Ever have any Bible training?

245
00:19:56,796 --> 00:19:59,098
- Yeah, as a matter of fact,

246
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:02,469
I took a correspondence
course once.

247
00:20:02,469 --> 00:20:03,303
- Hmm.

248
00:20:04,337 --> 00:20:05,605
Good.

249
00:20:05,605 --> 00:20:07,039
Anything beyond that?

250
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:08,541
- [Murell] Uh, no.

251
00:20:10,009 --> 00:20:12,945
- Okay, that pretty
 much covers it.

252
00:20:15,248 --> 00:20:16,983
Here, let me do this.

253
00:20:23,523 --> 00:20:26,326
Murell, how would you
 feel about leading

254
00:20:26,326 --> 00:20:28,961
the church youth group?

255
00:20:28,961 --> 00:20:32,198
- Hmm, well, I'd really
have to think about it.

256
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:34,601
- It's just temporary
 for a couple of months

257
00:20:34,601 --> 00:20:36,469
till we get our replacement.

258
00:20:36,469 --> 00:20:39,639
Give it some
 thought, sleep on it.

259
00:20:39,639 --> 00:20:41,974
Let me know what you decide.

260
00:20:43,175 --> 00:20:44,010
Sloane.

