00:53:21,899 --> 00:53:24,635
- Maybe we should
 just go with them.

773
00:53:28,273 --> 00:53:30,107
- All right, we'll go.

774
00:53:35,980 --> 00:53:38,683
- I hear this resort
 is pretty nice.

775
00:53:38,683 --> 00:53:41,786
They got a spa,
 jacuzzi, weight room.

776
00:53:43,288 --> 00:53:46,657
- I've been there
about five times, okay?

777
00:53:46,657 --> 00:53:47,492
- Oh.

778
00:53:49,226 --> 00:53:51,061
You know you guys have
 an awful lot of stuff

779
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:52,297
packed in those bags.

780
00:53:52,297 --> 00:53:55,733
I mean, where were
 you plannin' on goin'?

781
00:53:58,669 --> 00:54:01,171
(van rattling)

782
00:54:05,576 --> 00:54:08,746
- It sounds like
 something's wrong.

783
00:54:08,746 --> 00:54:11,749
(indicator beeping)

784
00:54:32,937 --> 00:54:36,006
- [Sheldon] What
 are we gonna do now?

785
00:54:37,508 --> 00:54:39,344
- Why don't we call a cab?

786
00:54:39,344 --> 00:54:42,413
- Oh, that's good,
 very good, Sloane.

787
00:54:44,515 --> 00:54:45,350
- Taxi!

788
00:54:51,288 --> 00:54:52,122
Taxi!

789
00:54:56,026 --> 00:54:59,564
- We could take a bus,
 except I don't think

790
00:54:59,564 --> 00:55:01,632
there are any buses.

791
00:55:01,632 --> 00:55:03,734
- Hold on, I got an idea.

792
00:55:05,370 --> 00:55:08,172
The shelter's just a
 few blocks from here.

793
00:55:08,172 --> 00:55:09,273
- What, the shelter?

794
00:55:09,273 --> 00:55:11,376
- Yeah, the Thompson House.

795
00:55:11,376 --> 00:55:15,546
We can hang out for a while,
 call for help, chill out.

796
00:55:16,614 --> 00:55:18,549
- Is it a homeless shelter?

797
00:55:18,549 --> 00:55:22,720
- Coke, smoke, coke, smoke,
 coke, smoke, coke coke, smoke.

798
00:55:27,825 --> 00:55:31,095
- So how far is that
 shelter from here?

799
00:55:34,331 --> 00:55:38,536
- Yeah, this used to be
my old stompin' ground.

800
00:55:38,536 --> 00:55:42,072
Me and Ray hung
 out all over here.

801
00:55:42,072 --> 00:55:44,675
(somber music)

802
00:55:49,380 --> 00:55:52,750
Man, this place is as
raggedy as it ever was.

803
00:55:52,750 --> 00:55:55,085
Hasn't improved not one bit.

804
00:55:57,321 --> 00:55:58,823
Lived in there for a while.

805
00:55:58,823 --> 00:56:01,592
Got inside, found
 an old mattress.

806
00:56:02,727 --> 00:56:05,062
Whew, it was pretty raunchy.

807
00:56:11,902 --> 00:56:15,005
Over back there,
 behind the dumpster,

808
00:56:16,373 --> 00:56:17,442
I used to uh,

809
00:56:19,810 --> 00:56:20,645
shoot up.

810
00:56:32,823 --> 00:56:35,560
- You guys can stay as
 long as you need to,

811
00:56:35,560 --> 00:56:38,963
but nobody lives here
without doin' some work.

812
00:56:38,963 --> 00:56:41,566
(upbeat music)

813
00:57:02,286 --> 00:57:06,457
- Dear God, thank you for
 bringing us here safely.

814
00:57:20,605 --> 00:57:21,606
- Excuse me.

815
00:57:26,443 --> 00:57:27,945
- Well, have a
 good sleep, George.

816
00:57:27,945 --> 00:57:29,446
I enjoyed talking with you.

817
00:57:29,446 --> 00:57:32,382
- Yeah, it was
 interesting anyways.

818
00:57:34,485 --> 00:57:38,122
Hey, Sloane, could
 you do me a favor?

819
00:57:38,122 --> 00:57:39,356
- What is it?

820
00:57:39,356 --> 00:57:41,792
- Could you um,
 well, never mind.

821
00:57:44,461 --> 00:57:47,264
Sloane, could you
 help tuck me in?

822
00:57:47,264 --> 00:57:48,666
- What?

823
00:57:48,666 --> 00:57:50,400
Am I supposed to be your
mother or something?

824
00:57:50,400 --> 00:57:52,402
- No, see I just can't reach.

825
00:57:52,402 --> 00:57:55,740
- Come on, grow up,
 for cryin' out loud!

826
00:57:56,574 --> 00:57:58,242
- Sloane, come here.

827
00:58:06,016 --> 00:58:09,319
Now, Sloane, you may
 think that George

828
00:58:09,319 --> 00:58:12,422
is kind of weird or
 odd or something,

829
00:58:13,591 --> 00:58:15,960
but you gotta be
 patient with him.

830
00:58:15,960 --> 00:58:20,497
He's a recovering alcoholic,
 and he needs friendship.

831
00:58:20,497 --> 00:58:22,166
He needs love.

832
00:58:22,166 --> 00:58:23,801
- Yeah, but I'm
 not a psychiatrist.

833
00:58:23,801 --> 00:58:25,302
This guy needs
 professional help.

834
00:58:25,302 --> 00:58:26,303
He's messed up.

835
00:58:26,303 --> 00:58:28,038
- Sloane, so are you.

836
00:58:29,373 --> 00:58:30,340
You are messed up.

837
00:58:30,340 --> 00:58:31,175
I'm messed up.

838
00:58:31,175 --> 00:58:33,578
We're all messed up.

839
00:58:33,578 --> 00:58:36,013
Isn't it possible to just
 step out of your skin

840
00:58:36,013 --> 00:58:39,483
and think about someone
besides yourself?

841
00:58:39,483 --> 00:58:40,785
Is it that hard?

842
00:58:51,395 --> 00:58:53,798
- Okay, I think we all agree.

843
00:58:54,832 --> 00:58:57,001
This is an experiment
 that failed.

844
00:58:57,001 --> 00:58:58,168
- Miserably.

845
00:58:58,168 --> 00:58:59,737
- That guy's dangerous.

846
00:58:59,737 --> 00:59:02,940
- Walter, we have to
 put an end to this.

847
00:59:02,940 --> 00:59:06,944
- Better pull the plug
 while there's still time.

848
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:13,217
(zippers sliding)

849
01:00:04,635 --> 01:00:07,237
- Sloane, what are you doin'?

850
01:00:07,237 --> 01:00:09,674
(drum music)

851
01:00:36,533 --> 01:00:37,367
- No!

852
01:00:55,385 --> 01:00:59,156
- You can't run from
 your problems, Sloane.

853
01:00:59,156 --> 01:01:00,758
- I would've if
 you didn't show up.

854
01:01:00,758 --> 01:01:04,494
- No, they'll just catch
up with you somehow.

855
01:01:05,696 --> 01:01:08,465
Sloane, what do you want?

856
01:01:08,465 --> 01:01:12,903
I mean, how's running
 away gonna solve anything?

857
01:01:12,903 --> 01:01:15,205
What are you looking for?

858
01:01:15,205 --> 01:01:17,607
- I just want a break.

859
01:01:17,607 --> 01:01:20,010
I'm sick of pretending.

860
01:01:20,010 --> 01:01:24,849
- Yeah, but why do you
 have to fight everything?

861
01:01:24,849 --> 01:01:25,850
Sloane, hey.

862
01:01:31,722 --> 01:01:35,159
You may have trouble
 believing this,

863
01:01:35,159 --> 01:01:37,194
but I've been there.

864
01:01:37,194 --> 01:01:39,363
I've been where you're at.

865
01:01:41,365 --> 01:01:43,367
I've been at the lowest spot,

866
01:01:43,367 --> 01:01:45,836
where the whole world
 seems pointless,

867
01:01:45,836 --> 01:01:48,172
and nothing matters.

868
01:01:48,172 --> 01:01:49,006
- So?

869
01:01:50,607 --> 01:01:55,212
- But I realized something,
 you can't keep running.

870
01:01:55,212 --> 01:01:57,181
You can't keep looking
for something artificial

871
01:01:57,181 --> 01:01:59,116
to solve your problems.

872
01:02:12,162 --> 01:02:14,731
I see you fightin', Sloane.

873
01:02:14,731 --> 01:02:18,502
You're fightin' me, your
 family, the whole world's

874
01:02:18,502 --> 01:02:20,437
on your shoulders, man.

875
01:02:21,738 --> 01:02:24,574
But it don't have
 to be like that.

876
01:02:26,176 --> 01:02:29,713
Jesus came down
 and gave his life.

877
01:02:29,713 --> 01:02:33,450
God sacrificed his own
 son so you could live.

878
01:02:35,519 --> 01:02:37,554
You don't have to fight anymore.

879
01:02:37,554 --> 01:02:42,026
- That's really great,
 but what if I don't care?

880
01:02:42,026 --> 01:02:44,528
- That's your choice.

881
01:02:44,528 --> 01:02:47,998
You have to decide
 which way to go.

882
01:02:47,998 --> 01:02:49,499
I can't force you.

883
01:02:51,101 --> 01:02:52,069
But why would you turn your back

884
01:02:52,069 --> 01:02:55,105
on the creator of the universe?

885
01:02:55,105 --> 01:02:57,641
- I've been through
 this already.

886
01:02:57,641 --> 01:02:59,676
When I was seven years old,
 I walked down the aisle.

887
01:02:59,676 --> 01:03:01,278
I went through the whole deal.

888
01:03:01,278 --> 01:03:04,581
- Yeah, but God wants
 more from you, Sloane.

889
01:03:04,581 --> 01:03:07,317
He wants to live in you.

890
01:03:07,317 --> 01:03:10,587
You've got to let
 Jesus plant his seed.

891
01:03:13,090 --> 01:03:15,525
- I don't think I'm
 capable of changing.

892
01:03:15,525 --> 01:03:19,763
- That's right, you've got
 to let Jesus do it for you.

893
01:03:19,763 --> 01:03:22,900
You've just got to
 give him a chance.

894
01:03:22,900 --> 01:03:24,801
Just give him a chance.

895
01:03:36,881 --> 01:03:38,548
- Please, God, help.

896
01:03:41,051 --> 01:03:44,354
(peaceful music)

897
01:03:44,354 --> 01:03:47,357
I'm sorry for running
 away from you.

898
01:03:48,893 --> 01:03:51,228
Help me turn my life around.

899
01:03:57,201 --> 01:04:00,270
Take my heart and
 clean it out, Lord.

900
01:04:06,743 --> 01:04:10,580
I give you all these
 hassles and expectations.

901
01:04:20,457 --> 01:04:22,626
Jesus, plant a seed in me,

902
01:04:27,965 --> 01:04:29,733
inside of me,

903
01:04:29,733 --> 01:04:31,969
let it grow into something,

904
01:04:36,440 --> 01:04:38,275
something you can use.

905
01:04:58,262 --> 01:05:00,230
- This doesn't
 look good, Walter.

906
01:05:00,230 --> 01:05:01,731
- Well, I figure it's
 better to get the problem

907
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:04,334
in the open rather
than letting it fester.

908
01:05:04,334 --> 01:05:06,736
- They look like a lynch mob.

909
01:05:22,219 --> 01:05:25,155
- Oh Murell, they're holding
 a meeting in the sanctuary.

910
01:05:25,155 --> 01:05:27,557
Pastor said he wants
 you there right away.

911
01:05:27,557 --> 01:05:28,625
- Right now?

912
01:05:28,625 --> 01:05:29,459
- Yeah.

913
01:06:01,458 --> 01:06:05,762
- Over the past weeks,
this church has endured

914
01:06:05,762 --> 01:06:09,566
some rather strange
 occurrences, and it is our

915
01:06:11,035 --> 01:06:14,371
intention to clear
 the air, so to speak,

916
01:06:17,441 --> 01:06:20,610
with this meeting
 of the congregation.

917
01:06:22,412 --> 01:06:24,348
- I'd just like to
know how a youth pastor

918
01:06:24,348 --> 01:06:27,251
can take a group to
 see an AIDS victim

919
01:06:27,251 --> 01:06:29,819
without consulting the
parents or anyone else?

920
01:06:29,819 --> 01:06:31,888
- And how could this
 man take our kids

921
01:06:31,888 --> 01:06:34,658
into a very dangerous
 section of the city,

922
01:06:34,658 --> 01:06:37,427
associating with drunks
and drug addicts,

923
01:06:37,427 --> 01:06:39,996
placing their lives at risk?

924
01:06:39,996 --> 01:06:42,466
- Let me just say that
 I deeply regret these

925
01:06:42,466 --> 01:06:45,702
incidents, and on
 behalf of the church,

926
01:06:46,836 --> 01:06:50,240
I apologize for
 what has transpired.

927
01:06:50,240 --> 01:06:54,010
Fortunately, however,
 Murell is here to directly

928
01:06:54,010 --> 01:06:57,013
address some of
 your concerns today.

929
01:07:10,727 --> 01:07:12,829
- Look, I just wanna say,

930
01:07:17,901 --> 01:07:20,904
I'm truly sorry
 about what happened.

931
01:07:22,772 --> 01:07:25,008
I made a lot of mistakes,

932
01:07:25,008 --> 01:07:27,411
and I'm responsible for them.

933
01:07:30,580 --> 01:07:34,584
But I was offered this
 position a few weeks ago,

934
01:07:36,986 --> 01:07:40,157
and I can honestly
 say, I did my best.

935
01:07:44,894 --> 01:07:47,897
I really tried to
 be a youth leader.

936
01:07:51,601 --> 01:07:55,004
I tried to share
something from my heart,

937
01:07:56,173 --> 01:07:59,876
but I won't stick around
where I'm not wanted.

938
01:08:02,912 --> 01:08:03,747
- Wait.

939
01:08:05,215 --> 01:08:07,851
This man made a difference.

940
01:08:07,851 --> 01:08:10,620
He really cared about us.

941
01:08:10,620 --> 01:08:12,556
He showed us something.

942
01:08:13,957 --> 01:08:16,193
- I don't think you're
 giving this man a chance.

943
01:08:16,193 --> 01:08:19,263
I've seen a way he's taken
 an interest in my son.

944
01:08:19,263 --> 01:08:23,167
He's given these kids
 some valuable lessons.

945
01:08:23,167 --> 01:08:25,269
- You can't get rid of him.

946
01:08:25,269 --> 01:08:28,071
He's been more than
 our youth leader.

947
01:08:28,071 --> 01:08:29,906
He's been our friend.

948
01:08:29,906 --> 01:08:31,241
He belongs here.

949
01:08:32,509 --> 01:08:35,845
- Murell has taught
 me more about Christ

950
01:08:37,214 --> 01:08:40,950
and how to love others
 than any person in my life.

951
01:08:42,286 --> 01:08:46,190
Dad, I know I screwed
up, and I promise to do

952
01:08:46,190 --> 01:08:49,693
better, just give this
 guy another chance.

953
01:08:51,728 --> 01:08:52,562
- Thanks.

954
01:08:54,097 --> 01:08:56,700
I really appreciate that, guys.

955
01:09:00,504 --> 01:09:02,972
I'm gonna miss you guys a lot,

956
01:09:04,574 --> 01:09:08,077
but I think it's really
time for me to go.

957
01:09:17,020 --> 01:09:19,623
(gentle music)

958
01:09:44,013 --> 01:09:45,849
- [Bobby] Hey, Murell!

959
01:09:47,884 --> 01:09:49,786
Where are you goin'?

960
01:09:49,786 --> 01:09:51,455
- Hey, guys.

961
01:09:51,455 --> 01:09:53,022
- Where you off to?

962
01:09:53,957 --> 01:09:57,126
- Gonna visit some old friends.

963
01:09:57,126 --> 01:09:59,629
- Without even saying goodbye?

964
01:10:25,922 --> 01:10:27,257
- Okay, Sheldon.

965
01:10:30,660 --> 01:10:32,329
- [Bobby] Thank you.

966
01:10:39,369 --> 01:10:40,804
- What about the youth group?

967
01:10:40,804 --> 01:10:42,138
How will it survive?

968
01:10:42,138 --> 01:10:45,141
- That's up to you
 and all you guys.

969
01:10:49,078 --> 01:10:51,915
Don't rely on
 anyone except Jesus.

970
01:10:55,519 --> 01:10:58,254
Here, I wanna give
 you something.

971
01:11:11,200 --> 01:11:13,603
- I'm gonna miss you, Murell.

972
01:11:44,668 --> 01:11:47,337
(strings music)

